    "department": "Client Service",
    "description": "MULESOFT DEVELOPER\n\n\nABOUT THE ROLE\n\nWe are looking for an Integration Engineer to design, build, and maintain reliable integrations between internal systems and third‑party automation platforms. This role focuses on API connectivity, event‑driven workflows, and automation reliability to support fast‑moving business processes. You will play a key role in enabling scalable, resilient system‑to‑system communication across the organization.\n\n\nWHAT YOU’LL DO\n\n - Build and maintain integrations between internal APIs and third‑party workflow automation platforms such as Gumloop, n8n, Langsmith, and similar tools\n\n - Develop and maintain API connectors, webhooks, and data transformation logic\n\n - Design and implement event‑driven workflows using webhook and asynchronous patterns\n\n - Monitor integration health, troubleshoot failures, and resolve performance issues\n\n - Ensure integrations are secure, reliable, and scalable\n\n - Collaborate with product, engineering, and operations teams to understand integration needs\n\n - Prioritize integration work based on business impact and urgency\n\n - Document integration workflows, APIs, and operational runbooks\n\n\nWHO YOU ARE\n\n - Strong familiarity with workflow automation tools or integration platforms\n\n - Hands-on experience building API integrations, webhooks, and data transformations\n\n - 5 years of hands-on experience with MuleSoft.\n\n - Practical experience with DataWeave.\n\n - Solid understanding of event‑driven architectures and asynchronous communication patterns\n\n - Comfortable debugging distributed systems and third‑party integrations\n\n - Able to balance technical execution with business priorities\n\n - Detail‑oriented, proactive, and ownership‑driven\n\n - Strong communication skills with both technical and non‑technical stakeholders\n\nAbout Riveron:\n\nAt Riveron, we partner with clients—from global multinationals to high-growth private entities—to solve complex finance challenges, guided by our DELTA values: Drive, Excellence, Leadership, Teamwork, and Accountability. Our entrepreneurial culture thrives on collaboration, diverse perspectives, and delivering exceptional outcomes. We are committed to fostering growth, both for our clients and our people, through mentorship, integrity, and a client-centric approach. This inclusive environment offers flexibility, progressive benefits, and meaningful opportunities for impactful work that supports well-being in and out of the office.\n\nCheck us out on social media:\n\nLinkedIn https://www.linkedin.com/company/riveron/life/culture/ Glassdoor https://www.glassdoor.com/Photos/Riveron-Office-Photos-E672242.htm Instagram https://www.instagram.com/riveronconsulting/ Facebook https://www.facebook.com/RiveronConsulting/\n\nRiveron Consulting is an Equal Opportunity Employer and believes that we are stronger together through our diversity. All qualified applicants will receive consideration for employment without regard to race, color, religion, sex, age, national origin, disability status, protected veteran status, sexual orientation, gender identity or any other characteristic protected by law.\n\nFull time roles are eligible for a full range of benefits including medical, dental, and vision insurance, 401(k) with company match, and PTO. A complete description of all available benefits can be found at Riveron's Benefits page at https://riveron.com/riveron-life/. Contract roles are not eligible for benefits.\n\n\nFRAUD ALERT\n\nPlease beware of fraudulent schemes or impersonations when going through the job application process. A Riveron employee will never recruit via text or extend unsolicited employment offers. Additionally, a Riveron employee will never ask you to exchange money or purchase anything as part of the recruiting process.\n\n\nWE MAY USE ARTIFICIAL INTELLIGENCE (AI) TOOLS TO SUPPORT PARTS OF THE HIRING PROCESS, SUCH AS REVIEWING APPLICATIONS, ANALYZING RESUMES, OR ASSESSING RESPONSES. THESE TOOLS ASSIST OUR RECRUITMENT TEAM BUT DO NOT REPLACE HUMAN JUDGMENT. FINAL HIRING DECISIONS ARE ULTIMATELY MADE BY HUMANS. IF YOU WOULD LIKE MORE INFORMATION ABOUT HOW YOUR DATA IS PROCESSED, PLEASE CONTACT US.",
